<p>In case it's useful to really see there is no difference between <code>string</code> and <code>System.String</code>:</p>

<pre><code>var method1 = typeof(MyClass).GetMethod("TestString1").GetMethodBody().GetILAsByteArray();
var method2 = typeof(MyClass).GetMethod("TestString2").GetMethodBody().GetILAsByteArray();

//...

public string TestString1()
{
    string str = "Hello World!";
    return str;
}

public string TestString2()
{
    String str = "Hello World!";
    return str;
}
</code></pre>

<p>Both produce exactly the same IL byte array:</p>

<pre><code>[ 0, 114, 107, 0, 0, 112, 10, 6, 11, 43, 0, 7, 42 ]
</code></pre>
